In selectPage method body, adding the typical 

`if ($event) {
  $event.preventDefault();
}`

prevents the pagenavigating to anchor if ng-href="#" directive is used on pager buttons in a custom template. The use of this directive displays the cursor mouse pointer instead of the text mouse pointer, which is desirable.

The following code results in an error:

> UnsupportedSyntaxError: Node type 'For': ... . Target must be a name, Are you sure is only one?

```python
some_dict = dict()
for key, value in some_dict.items():
  # ...
```

Transcrypt for example is translating this to:
```javascript
for (var [key, value] of some_dict.py_items()) {
  // ...
}
```

An alternative would perhaps be:
```javascript
Object.keys(some_dict).forEach(key => {
  const value = some_dict[key];
  // ...
}
```

