##### ISSUE TYPE
<!--- Pick one below and delete the rest: -->
 - Bug Report

##### OS
Linux, 4.4, Ubuntu Trusty

##### VERSION
<!--- Paste verbatim the output from “exabgp --version” between quotes below -->
```
ExaBGP : 3.4.17
Python : 2.7.6 (default, Oct 26 2016, 20:30:19)  [GCC 4.8.4]
Uname  : #96~14.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Thu Apr 20 11:06:30 UTC 2017
```

##### ENVIRONMENT 
<!--- Paste verbatim the output from “exabgp --di” (let us know if the output is empty) between quotes below -->
```
exabgp --di

[exabgp.daemon]
user = 'exabgp'
```

<!--- You can also use gist.github.com links for larger files -->

##### CONFIGURATION
```
group ALL_PEERS {
        router-id 78.140.148.33;
        local-address 78.140.148.33;
        process add_route {
                run /usr/bin/announce-processor-wrapper;
                encoder text;
                receive {
                        update;
                        parsed;
                }
                neighbor-changes;
        }
        neighbor 8.8.8.8 {
            local-as 40824;
            peer-as 46786;
                        md5-password ZGIwMzk3MmEtMjljMC0xMWU3LWJiMDMtY2IzYTM5NjJkNDdk;
                        md5-base64 true;
                }
        }

```

##### SUMMARY
<!--- Explain the problem briefly -->

This configuration cause exabgp to set md5 variable in exabgp/reactor/network/tcp.py (MD5 function) to `'-base64 true'`, which cause problems with authorization. Same applied if I use `'md5-password "mypassword"'` - in this case md5 would become `'-password "mypassword"'`, which is clearly wrong.

We spend few hours trying to understand why md5 auth does not work. We set it up according to this link:https://github.com/Exa-Networks/exabgp/blob/4d11197e0ad950f0173d4da0f5a35a1b6cc301bf/qa/conf/md5.conf

